WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:00.800 align:middle line:90%


00:00:00.800 --> 00:00:02.425 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:02.425 --> 00:00:22.253 align:middle line:90%


00:00:22.253 --> 00:00:26.080 align:middle line:10%
>> One might object that this
evidence is drawn from outdated

00:00:26.080 --> 00:00:30.310 align:middle line:10%
reports, but what about the
recent discoveries in Africa

00:00:30.310 --> 00:00:33.760 align:middle line:10%
that seem to clearly establish
the evolution of humans from

00:00:33.760 --> 00:00:37.930 align:middle line:10%
ape-like creatures over the
past three million years?

00:00:37.930 --> 00:00:42.100 align:middle line:84%
In 1978 at Laetoli,
Kenya, an expedition

00:00:42.100 --> 00:00:45.040 align:middle line:84%
headed by Mary Leakey
discovered fossil footprints

00:00:45.040 --> 00:00:48.130 align:middle line:90%
dated 3.7 million years old.

00:00:48.130 --> 00:00:51.580 align:middle line:84%
Here is a contour map
of one of the prints.

00:00:51.580 --> 00:00:53.980 align:middle line:84%
Many scientists who
have studied the prints

00:00:53.980 --> 00:00:56.620 align:middle line:84%
declare they are
indistinguishable from those

00:00:56.620 --> 00:00:58.900 align:middle line:90%
of modern man.

00:00:58.900 --> 00:01:01.570 align:middle line:84%
This three-dimensional
image was generated

00:01:01.570 --> 00:01:05.019 align:middle line:90%
from the contour map just seen.

00:01:05.019 --> 00:01:08.490 align:middle line:84%
Could this print have been
made by a human being?

00:01:08.490 --> 00:01:11.710 align:middle line:84%
To most scientists,
the answer is no.

00:01:11.710 --> 00:01:15.280 align:middle line:84%
Instead, the Laetoli footprints
are taken as evidence

00:01:15.280 --> 00:01:19.420 align:middle line:84%
that Australopithecus had
feet like modern humans.

00:01:19.420 --> 00:01:22.810 align:middle line:84%
Indeed, Australopithecus is
said to have been fully human

00:01:22.810 --> 00:01:24.050 align:middle line:90%
below its ape-like head.

00:01:24.050 --> 00:01:26.880 align:middle line:90%


00:01:26.880 --> 00:01:31.080 align:middle line:84%
But some scientists have come up
with quite a different picture.

00:01:31.080 --> 00:01:33.900 align:middle line:84%
The hand bones of the
Australopithecines

00:01:33.900 --> 00:01:38.580 align:middle line:84%
suggest to anatomical experts,
such as CE Oxnard, that they

00:01:38.580 --> 00:01:40.980 align:middle line:84%
were well adapted
to moving in trees

00:01:40.980 --> 00:01:43.612 align:middle line:84%
in a manner similar to
the modern orangutan.

00:01:43.612 --> 00:01:46.270 align:middle line:90%


00:01:46.270 --> 00:01:48.220 align:middle line:84%
Let's compare the
blue silhouette

00:01:48.220 --> 00:01:51.790 align:middle line:84%
of the Australopithecus hand
with the green silhouette

00:01:51.790 --> 00:01:54.535 align:middle line:90%
of the hand of the orangutan.

00:01:54.535 --> 00:01:59.540 align:middle line:84%
The finger bones are strongly
curved in both hands.

00:01:59.540 --> 00:02:02.870 align:middle line:84%
Let's now compare the
Australopithecus hand

00:02:02.870 --> 00:02:06.150 align:middle line:84%
with that of the
chimpanzee in brown.

00:02:06.150 --> 00:02:10.190 align:middle line:84%
The chimp's finger bones
are somewhat straighter.

00:02:10.190 --> 00:02:13.220 align:middle line:84%
Finally, we compare the
Australopithecus hand

00:02:13.220 --> 00:02:16.210 align:middle line:84%
to that of Homo
sapiens in purple.

00:02:16.210 --> 00:02:20.270 align:middle line:84%
The human finger bones
are even straighter.

00:02:20.270 --> 00:02:24.050 align:middle line:84%
Hominoids with curved finger
bones, such as orangutans,

00:02:24.050 --> 00:02:27.650 align:middle line:84%
are very active in trees,
whereas human beings

00:02:27.650 --> 00:02:30.380 align:middle line:84%
with straight finger
bones are not.

00:02:30.380 --> 00:02:33.440 align:middle line:84%
This suggests that
Australopithecus was well

00:02:33.440 --> 00:02:35.780 align:middle line:90%
adapted to life in trees.

00:02:35.780 --> 00:02:39.020 align:middle line:84%
The hip bone of the
Australopithecine Lucy,

00:02:39.020 --> 00:02:41.840 align:middle line:84%
now thought to be at the very
root of the lineage leading

00:02:41.840 --> 00:02:46.510 align:middle line:84%
to man, has often been described
as nearly human in form.

00:02:46.510 --> 00:02:50.050 align:middle line:84%
This is also true of
the Sterkfontein pelvis,

00:02:50.050 --> 00:02:53.770 align:middle line:84%
also from the Australopithecus,
shown here along

00:02:53.770 --> 00:02:55.360 align:middle line:90%
with the human pelvis.

00:02:55.360 --> 00:02:59.480 align:middle line:84%
Note the similarity of the
upper parts, the iliac blades.

00:02:59.480 --> 00:03:03.280 align:middle line:84%
But if we look at these bones in
an orientation in which the hip

00:03:03.280 --> 00:03:07.180 align:middle line:84%
sockets are visible, we see
that the iliac blades are

00:03:07.180 --> 00:03:09.920 align:middle line:90%
set at very different angles.

00:03:09.920 --> 00:03:12.400 align:middle line:84%
Comparing the
Sterkfontein pelvic bone

00:03:12.400 --> 00:03:16.330 align:middle line:84%
with that of a chimpanzee,
we see in this orientation

00:03:16.330 --> 00:03:19.150 align:middle line:84%
that both bones
look quite similar

00:03:19.150 --> 00:03:22.060 align:middle line:84%
and are both different
from the human pelvis.

00:03:22.060 --> 00:03:26.170 align:middle line:84%
In frontal orientation, the
Australopithecus and ape bones

00:03:26.170 --> 00:03:28.630 align:middle line:90%
look quite dissimilar.

00:03:28.630 --> 00:03:31.660 align:middle line:84%
The tentative conclusion is
that the Australopithecus

00:03:31.660 --> 00:03:35.350 align:middle line:84%
pelvis shares both strongly
ape-like and strongly

00:03:35.350 --> 00:03:37.830 align:middle line:90%
human-like features.

00:03:37.830 --> 00:03:41.750 align:middle line:84%
Now let's turn to the
mathematical analysis of bones.

00:03:41.750 --> 00:03:44.090 align:middle line:84%
Measuring different
parts of the bone,

00:03:44.090 --> 00:03:47.150 align:middle line:84%
one can represent
its shape as a point

00:03:47.150 --> 00:03:49.190 align:middle line:90%
in a multi-dimensional space.

00:03:49.190 --> 00:03:52.010 align:middle line:84%
Here, two measurements
of a human thigh bone

00:03:52.010 --> 00:03:55.520 align:middle line:84%
define a corresponding
point in two dimensions.

00:03:55.520 --> 00:03:58.430 align:middle line:84%
Relations between bones
of different species

00:03:58.430 --> 00:04:01.430 align:middle line:84%
can be studied by comparing
the corresponding points

00:04:01.430 --> 00:04:03.930 align:middle line:90%
in multi-dimensional space.

00:04:03.930 --> 00:04:08.010 align:middle line:84%
Let's consider a study by
CE Oxnard on the ankle bones

00:04:08.010 --> 00:04:09.750 align:middle line:90%
of various hominids.

00:04:09.750 --> 00:04:13.020 align:middle line:84%
Here is the ankle
bone of a modern human

00:04:13.020 --> 00:04:17.350 align:middle line:84%
and that of an
Australopithecine, namely Lucy.

00:04:17.350 --> 00:04:19.420 align:middle line:84%
The distances
between the spheres

00:04:19.420 --> 00:04:21.040 align:middle line:84%
represent the
amount of difference

00:04:21.040 --> 00:04:24.730 align:middle line:84%
between the ankle bones
of humans in yellow,

00:04:24.730 --> 00:04:30.020 align:middle line:84%
apes in green, and
Australopithecines in purple.

00:04:30.020 --> 00:04:33.530 align:middle line:84%
Curiously, the blue sphere
representing the orangutan

00:04:33.530 --> 00:04:36.020 align:middle line:84%
lies among the
Australopithecines,

00:04:36.020 --> 00:04:39.920 align:middle line:84%
which are distinct from both
modern man and African apes

00:04:39.920 --> 00:04:42.560 align:middle line:84%
and not intermediate
between them.

00:04:42.560 --> 00:04:45.110 align:middle line:84%
Some have said that
Australopithecines

00:04:45.110 --> 00:04:48.380 align:middle line:84%
are intermediate between
African apes and men,

00:04:48.380 --> 00:04:51.610 align:middle line:84%
but this analysis shows them
to be in a domain of their own

00:04:51.610 --> 00:04:54.060 align:middle line:84%
with structural affinities
with orangutans.

00:04:54.060 --> 00:04:56.730 align:middle line:90%


00:04:56.730 --> 00:04:59.880 align:middle line:84%
JP [INAUDIBLE] performed
a multivariate study

00:04:59.880 --> 00:05:03.690 align:middle line:84%
of metacarpal bones from
the hands of humans, apes,

00:05:03.690 --> 00:05:05.520 align:middle line:90%
and Australopithecus.

00:05:05.520 --> 00:05:08.430 align:middle line:84%
His studies showed that
Australopithecus' metacarpal,

00:05:08.430 --> 00:05:12.150 align:middle line:84%
purple, is not intermediate
between that of humans,

00:05:12.150 --> 00:05:17.340 align:middle line:84%
yellow, and African apes, green,
but is morphologically unique.

00:05:17.340 --> 00:05:20.160 align:middle line:90%


00:05:20.160 --> 00:05:22.620 align:middle line:84%
Like Australopithecus,
Homo habilis

00:05:22.620 --> 00:05:24.630 align:middle line:84%
is shown in both
scientific studies

00:05:24.630 --> 00:05:28.800 align:middle line:84%
and popular presentations
as having an ape-like head

00:05:28.800 --> 00:05:31.000 align:middle line:90%
and a human body.

00:05:31.000 --> 00:05:33.810 align:middle line:84%
This picture is redrawn
from an original painting

00:05:33.810 --> 00:05:37.086 align:middle line:84%
by Jay Matternes in
"National Geographic."

00:05:37.086 --> 00:05:38.460 align:middle line:84%
According to the
studies, we have

00:05:38.460 --> 00:05:41.160 align:middle line:84%
considered this is
a misrepresentation

00:05:41.160 --> 00:05:42.510 align:middle line:90%
of the evidence.

00:05:42.510 --> 00:05:45.070 align:middle line:84%
This is confirmed by
a recent discovery

00:05:45.070 --> 00:05:48.750 align:middle line:84%
in Olduvai Gorge in Kenya
of the first associated head

00:05:48.750 --> 00:05:50.970 align:middle line:90%
and limb bones of Homo habilis.

00:05:50.970 --> 00:05:52.950 align:middle line:84%
Here is what Homo
habilis is thought

00:05:52.950 --> 00:05:55.740 align:middle line:84%
to look like on the
basis of the new find.

00:05:55.740 --> 00:06:00.180 align:middle line:84%
And Australopithecus may have
appeared even more ape-like.

00:06:00.180 --> 00:06:03.480 align:middle line:84%
In view of this, certain
human-like thigh bones

00:06:03.480 --> 00:06:06.180 align:middle line:84%
once attributed to
Homo habilis must now

00:06:06.180 --> 00:06:09.360 align:middle line:90%
belong to some other creature.

00:06:09.360 --> 00:06:14.310 align:middle line:84%
These are at least
1.8 million years old.

00:06:14.310 --> 00:06:17.850 align:middle line:84%
Could it be that these
were actually human?

00:06:17.850 --> 00:06:21.120 align:middle line:84%
This might also be true in this
very ancient and human-like

00:06:21.120 --> 00:06:23.790 align:middle line:84%
upper arm bone found
in Kanapoi, Kenya.

00:06:23.790 --> 00:06:26.700 align:middle line:84%
In view of the great difference
between Australopithecus

00:06:26.700 --> 00:06:29.310 align:middle line:84%
and modern man,
what kind of being

00:06:29.310 --> 00:06:31.060 align:middle line:84%
could have possessed
this arm bone

00:06:31.060 --> 00:06:34.500 align:middle line:90%
four to five million years ago?

00:06:34.500 --> 00:06:36.150 align:middle line:84%
Could it have been
the same being

00:06:36.150 --> 00:06:39.960 align:middle line:84%
that made the human-like
footprints in Laetoli?

00:06:39.960 --> 00:06:42.330 align:middle line:84%
Overall, the evidence
does not appear

00:06:42.330 --> 00:06:44.850 align:middle line:84%
to support the view
that Australopithecines

00:06:44.850 --> 00:06:46.890 align:middle line:84%
were human ancestors'
intermediate

00:06:46.890 --> 00:06:49.860 align:middle line:84%
between the African
apes and man.

00:06:49.860 --> 00:06:53.130 align:middle line:84%
It is more likely that they
were unique creatures, rather

00:06:53.130 --> 00:06:55.080 align:middle line:84%
different from
both apes and men,

00:06:55.080 --> 00:06:57.630 align:middle line:84%
but with some tree
climbing adaptations

00:06:57.630 --> 00:07:01.470 align:middle line:90%
reminiscent of orangutans.

00:07:01.470 --> 00:07:04.290 align:middle line:84%
A careful review of the
modern African evidence

00:07:04.290 --> 00:07:06.810 align:middle line:84%
reveals nothing that
detracts from the picture

00:07:06.810 --> 00:07:08.870 align:middle line:84%
of great human
antiquity presented

00:07:08.870 --> 00:07:12.070 align:middle line:84%
in the first part of this
film and even provides

00:07:12.070 --> 00:07:14.160 align:middle line:84%
some directly
supporting evidence

00:07:14.160 --> 00:07:19.170 align:middle line:84%
in the form of human-like
footprints and fossil bones.

00:07:19.170 --> 00:07:22.290 align:middle line:84%
But a great controversy
exists in the interpretation

00:07:22.290 --> 00:07:25.350 align:middle line:84%
of this fragmentary
African evidence.

00:07:25.350 --> 00:07:28.850 align:middle line:84%
The more intently one
studies it, the more it

00:07:28.850 --> 00:07:32.810 align:middle line:84%
seems like trying to receive a
desired image in a flickering

00:07:32.810 --> 00:07:34.700 align:middle line:90%
mirage of possibilities.

00:07:34.700 --> 00:07:38.490 align:middle line:90%


00:07:38.490 --> 00:07:41.040 align:middle line:84%
The origin of man's
cultural traits

00:07:41.040 --> 00:07:43.230 align:middle line:84%
is perhaps even more
difficult to account

00:07:43.230 --> 00:07:46.170 align:middle line:84%
for than his
physical attributes.

00:07:46.170 --> 00:07:48.510 align:middle line:84%
This led Alfred Russell
Wallace to doubt

00:07:48.510 --> 00:07:53.130 align:middle line:84%
the standard conception
of human evolution.

00:07:53.130 --> 00:07:57.840 align:middle line:84%
Born in England in 1823, Wallace
shared with Darwin credit

00:07:57.840 --> 00:08:01.410 align:middle line:84%
for the theory of evolution
by natural selection.

00:08:01.410 --> 00:08:04.680 align:middle line:10%
Wallace could not explain
by natural selection

00:08:04.680 --> 00:08:07.890 align:middle line:10%
how people living in
simple tribal societies

00:08:07.890 --> 00:08:11.700 align:middle line:10%
acquired intellectual capacities
as great as those of a learned

00:08:11.700 --> 00:08:13.680 align:middle line:10%
Englishman of his time.

00:08:13.680 --> 00:08:19.230 align:middle line:84%
Wallace arrived at a heretical
conclusion, guided evolution.

00:08:19.230 --> 00:08:22.260 align:middle line:84%
He postulated the
existence of subtle beings

00:08:22.260 --> 00:08:24.360 align:middle line:84%
capable of
intelligently directing

00:08:24.360 --> 00:08:25.760 align:middle line:90%
the evolutionary process.

00:08:25.760 --> 00:08:28.630 align:middle line:90%


00:08:28.630 --> 00:08:30.940 align:middle line:90%
Darwin was aghast.

00:08:30.940 --> 00:08:34.600 align:middle line:84%
He wrote to Wallace that,
by propounding such notions,

00:08:34.600 --> 00:08:37.659 align:middle line:84%
he had literally murdered
their common child,

00:08:37.659 --> 00:08:40.690 align:middle line:90%
the theory of evolution.

00:08:40.690 --> 00:08:44.260 align:middle line:84%
But years later in South
Africa, a similar heresy

00:08:44.260 --> 00:08:45.760 align:middle line:90%
was propounded.

00:08:45.760 --> 00:08:47.920 align:middle line:84%
Dr. Robert Broom,
who had made many

00:08:47.920 --> 00:08:50.950 align:middle line:84%
of the most important South
African Australopithecus

00:08:50.950 --> 00:08:54.100 align:middle line:84%
discoveries, also
concluded that there

00:08:54.100 --> 00:08:57.580 align:middle line:84%
was a hierarchy of several
intelligent beings guiding

00:08:57.580 --> 00:09:00.880 align:middle line:90%
the process of evolution.

00:09:00.880 --> 00:09:03.580 align:middle line:84%
In light of the questions
that troubled Wallace,

00:09:03.580 --> 00:09:07.330 align:middle line:84%
consider the following
strange story.

00:09:07.330 --> 00:09:10.060 align:middle line:84%
According to current
thinking, culture

00:09:10.060 --> 00:09:14.500 align:middle line:84%
remained at a very crude
level for two million years.

00:09:14.500 --> 00:09:19.150 align:middle line:84%
Even with the rise of fully
modern man 40,000 years ago,

00:09:19.150 --> 00:09:21.670 align:middle line:90%
culture remained primitive.

00:09:21.670 --> 00:09:26.350 align:middle line:84%
Then about 7,000 years ago,
a radical transformation

00:09:26.350 --> 00:09:29.570 align:middle line:90%
is said to have occurred.

00:09:29.570 --> 00:09:32.630 align:middle line:84%
In the space of a few
centuries, civilizations

00:09:32.630 --> 00:09:35.210 align:middle line:84%
sprang into being
with the creation

00:09:35.210 --> 00:09:39.440 align:middle line:84%
of elaborate economic and
legal systems, architecture,

00:09:39.440 --> 00:09:44.660 align:middle line:84%
fine arts, and numerous
technological innovations.

00:09:44.660 --> 00:09:48.040 align:middle line:84%
In our own times, we find
that such developments

00:09:48.040 --> 00:09:51.595 align:middle line:84%
are due to people with strong
inborn creative talents.

00:09:51.595 --> 00:09:54.460 align:middle line:90%


00:09:54.460 --> 00:09:56.230 align:middle line:84%
The apparently
independent appearance

00:09:56.230 --> 00:09:59.110 align:middle line:84%
of civilization in
many parts of the world

00:09:59.110 --> 00:10:02.890 align:middle line:84%
suggests that such creative
drives are an innate feature

00:10:02.890 --> 00:10:04.960 align:middle line:90%
of Homo sapiens.

00:10:04.960 --> 00:10:07.600 align:middle line:84%
But how did these
talents arise and why

00:10:07.600 --> 00:10:11.470 align:middle line:84%
were they unexpressed
for at least 35,000 years

00:10:11.470 --> 00:10:13.380 align:middle line:84%
after the time of
the Cro-Magnon man?

00:10:13.380 --> 00:10:16.800 align:middle line:90%


00:10:16.800 --> 00:10:20.850 align:middle line:10%
Surprisingly, we find evidence
that civilization may not

00:10:20.850 --> 00:10:22.770 align:middle line:10%
be so recent.

00:10:22.770 --> 00:10:26.160 align:middle line:84%
The evidence for human
antiquity discussed so far

00:10:26.160 --> 00:10:31.270 align:middle line:84%
has all been published in
the scientific journals,

00:10:31.270 --> 00:10:34.390 align:middle line:84%
but now we shall cross
the boundaries of science

00:10:34.390 --> 00:10:37.310 align:middle line:84%
and enter the domain of
general human testimony.

00:10:37.310 --> 00:10:41.800 align:middle line:90%


00:10:41.800 --> 00:10:45.100 align:middle line:10%
According to this
newspaper from the 1890s,

00:10:45.100 --> 00:10:49.780 align:middle line:10%
Mrs. SW Culp found a gold
chain within a lump of coal.

00:10:49.780 --> 00:10:53.560 align:middle line:10%
This coal is dated by the
Geological Survey of Illinois

00:10:53.560 --> 00:10:59.290 align:middle line:10%
as being from 260 to
320 million years old.

00:10:59.290 --> 00:11:03.790 align:middle line:10%
In 1897, the miners at the
Lehigh Coal Mine in Iowa

00:11:03.790 --> 00:11:07.840 align:middle line:10%
found a stone engraved with
identical bas relief heads.

00:11:07.840 --> 00:11:11.630 align:middle line:10%
The coal in this mine dates
from the Carboniferous period,

00:11:11.630 --> 00:11:16.990 align:middle line:10%
some 280 to 360 million
years ago, during which time

00:11:16.990 --> 00:11:20.020 align:middle line:10%
amphibians were thought to be
the most advanced vertebrate

00:11:20.020 --> 00:11:21.250 align:middle line:10%
life form.

00:11:21.250 --> 00:11:24.760 align:middle line:84%
In 1862, the "LaSalle
Press" reported

00:11:24.760 --> 00:11:27.010 align:middle line:84%
that in Macoupin
County, Illinois,

00:11:27.010 --> 00:11:29.500 align:middle line:84%
90 feet beneath the
ground below two

00:11:29.500 --> 00:11:33.430 align:middle line:84%
feet of slate rock on a
coal bed, the bones of a man

00:11:33.430 --> 00:11:34.570 align:middle line:90%
were found.

00:11:34.570 --> 00:11:36.760 align:middle line:84%
The Geological
Survey of Illinois

00:11:36.760 --> 00:11:40.050 align:middle line:84%
dated this coal to the
Carboniferous period.

00:11:40.050 --> 00:11:45.580 align:middle line:84%
The human bones would thus be
about 300 million years old.

00:11:45.580 --> 00:11:49.450 align:middle line:10%
In 1912, Frank J.
Kenwood found an iron pot

00:11:49.450 --> 00:11:52.720 align:middle line:10%
embedded in a lump of coal at
the Municipal Electric power

00:11:52.720 --> 00:11:55.120 align:middle line:10%
plant in Thomas, Oklahoma.

00:11:55.120 --> 00:11:58.060 align:middle line:10%
The coal came from the
Wilburton Mines in Oklahoma

00:11:58.060 --> 00:12:00.900 align:middle line:10%
and is dated by the
Oklahoma Geological Survey

00:12:00.900 --> 00:12:02.310 align:middle line:10%
